THE SECURITY guard who allegedly sexually assaulted 87
school girls at a Soweto primary school will appear in the Protea Magistrate's
Court in Soweto.When the story initially made headlines, the number of
pupils alleged to have been sexually assaulted was 54, but the number later
rose to 87.During his last appearance on October 18, State prosecutor
Cheryl Slack asked for the matter to be postponed for further investigations to
